Describe a time when you shared something with others
- what you shared
- who you shared it with
- why you shared it
- explain how you felt about sharing it

I’d like to talk about a time when I shared a room with one of my close friends, An, about six years ago. At that time, I had just moved to Ho Chi Minh City to start university, and since living costs were quite high, I decided to find a roommate to share expenses.

Luckily, An, who was a friend from high school, was also moving to the city for his studies, and his university was quite close to mine. So we agreed to live together and eventually found a reasonably priced, medium-sized apartment.

Living with An was a really positive experience. He was very clean and organized, and we often shared household responsibilities, which made daily life much easier. He also had a great sense of humor and would frequently share funny videos or jokes, which helped me relax after a long day. On top of that, he played the guitar quite well, and sometimes we would sing together just for fun.

We lived together for over a year and created many great memories, from studying and cooking together to going out for coffee on weekends. Unfortunately, one day his mother asked him to move in with his aunt, so he had to leave the apartment.

I remember feeling quite upset at the time because I had grown so used to having him around. However, even though we no longer live together, we still keep in touch regularly through social media. Looking back, I feel really grateful for that experience, as it not only helped me save money but also strengthened our friendship.
